TI  - EMPIRICAL STUDY OF ECO-TRANSLATOLOGY FOR SCENIC SPOT IN CHINA BASED ON COGNITIVE SCHEMA THEORY - A CASE STUDY OF MOUNT SONG WORLD GEO-PARK
PY  - 2019
JO  - JOURNAL OF ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION AND ECOLOGY
AB  - Based on Image Schema Theory and Eco-translatology theory, this paper cites English introductions of Mount Song World Geo-park as a case study to illustrate the translation process in which the translator activates the schema of source language, constructs the contrastive schema between source language and target language and makes adaptive selection of the target language in terms of linguistic, cultural and communicative dimensions. Basic principles and translation strategies for scenic spot translation are proposed so as to broaden the comprehensive study of eco-translatology and cognitive linguistics, providing constructive reference for other relevant studies.
